# BDS Final Year Exam Prep — AP 2026

## Project Context
This is a study-aid web app for BDS (Bachelor of Dental Surgery) Final Year students appearing for university exams in Andhra Pradesh, India (March–April 2026). The goal is to provide quick-reference Q&A with simple analogies, mermaid mind maps, progress tracking (localStorage then Gmail/Supabase), and an exam countdown/planner. **Extended context**: see `docs/PROJECT-CONTEXT.md`. **Roadmap (stages)**: `docs/ROADMAP.md`. **Google OAuth (Supabase + Vercel)**: `docs/AUTH-GOOGLE-OAUTH.md`.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Astro 5 with React islands (interactive components)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **Diagrams**: Mermaid.js rendered client-side
- **Deployment**: Vercel (static output)

## Architecture
- `src/lib/subjects.ts` → Single source of truth for subject metadata & exam schedule
- `src/content/subjects/<slug>.json` → Per-subject content (questions, mind maps). **This is where you write content.**
- `src/components/` → React islands hydrated via `client:load` or `client:visible`
- `src/pages/` → Astro pages. `subjects/[slug].astro` is the dynamic subject detail page.

## Content Schema (per-subject JSON)
Each file in `src/content/subjects/` must follow this structure:
```json
{
  "slug": "subject-slug",
  "questions": [
    {
      "id": "unique-id",
      "topic": "Topic Name",
      "question": "Question text",
      "answer": "Concise, exam-ready answer",
      "analogy": "Simple real-world analogy to remember this concept",
      "highYield": true,
      "yearsAsked": ["2024", "2022"]
    }
  ],
  "mindMaps": [
    {
      "id": "unique-id",
      "title": "Concept Map Title",
      "mermaid": "graph TD\\n  A[Start] --> B[End]",
      "relatedQuestionIds": ["question-id"]
    }
  ]
}
```

## Key Rules
1. **Analogies**: Every answer should have a simple, relatable analogy (kitchen, sports, daily life). Students in AP relate well to Telugu cultural context — use when natural.
2. **High Yield**: Mark questions that have been repeated in previous university exams across AP/NTR university/KNRUHS papers.
3. **Mind Maps**: Use mermaid `graph TD` or `graph LR` for concept hierarchies. Keep nodes short (3–5 words max).
4. **Answers**: Exam-ready — structured, concise, but complete enough to score. Include classifications, key points, clinical significance.
5. **Mobile first**: Most students will access on phones. All components must work on 320px+ viewports.

## PDF Sources (in Downloads/BDS/)
These PDFs contain previous year questions and notes:
- Prosthodontics.pdf, prostho (1).pdf
- CONS & ENDO (1).pdf, Conservative Dentistry.pdf
- OMFS (1).pdf, Oral Surgery.pdf
- Community Dentistry.pdf
- Oral Medicine.pdf, OMR (1).pdf
- Pedodontics.pdf, phd pdf (1).pdf
- Orthodontics.pdf, ortho(1) (1).pdf
- Periodontology.pdf, perio (1).pdf, Periodontics.pdf

## Content Generation Workflow
1. Read all PDFs for a subject
2. Extract and deduplicate questions
3. Identify high-yield topics (repeated 2+ times)
4. Write concise exam-ready answers
5. Add memorable analogies
6. Create mermaid mind maps linking related concepts
7. Output as JSON matching the schema above

## Steelman decisions (applied)
- **Content loading**: Normalize after import (Array.isArray) so malformed JSON never breaks the UI; show empty state when subject has no questions/mindMaps.
- **All-exams-done**: When nextSubject is null and completed === total, show a short "All exams done" / congratulations hero instead of blank; same on Planner with a banner.
- **Answer formatting**: Answers may use **bold**; QAAccordion renders **...** as <strong> for readability (no full markdown).
- **Accessibility**: Skip link, aria-expanded/aria-controls/aria-label on accordion and filter buttons, diagram role="img" + aria-label, loading state for Mermaid so content is announced.
- **Planner**: Compute minDaysUpcoming once to avoid Math.min(...[]) when all exams are past.
